        <p>All HTML headings, <code>h1</code> through <code>h6</code>, are available. .h1 through .h6 classes are also available, for when you want to match the font styling of a heading but still want your text to be displayed inline.</p>
        <div class="row m-t-30">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <h1>Heading One</h1>
            <h2>Heading Two</h2>
            <h3>Heading Three</h3>
            <h4>Heading Four</h4>
            <h5>Heading Five</h5>
            <h6>Heading Six</h6>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <h1 class="font-weight-300">Heading One</h1>
            <h2 class="font-weight-300">Heading Two</h2>
            <h3 class="font-weight-300">Heading Three</h3>
            <h4 class="font-weight-300">Heading Four</h4>
